        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-07-20T21:00:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Empowering Parents and Teachers for a Drug-Free Education Act of 2004 - Amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 (under provisions which are also known as the Safe and Drug-Free Schools and Communities Act) to authorize the Secretary of Education to make grants to local educational agencies and private schools to establish drug-free school demonstration programs that include random drug testing of students and meet other specified requirements.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
